: A team of parliamentarians led by M. Thampi Durai, Lok Sabha Deputy Speaker and chairman of Members of Parliament Local Area Development Scheme, arrived here on Saturday to evaluate the development works implemented using local area development funds by MPs. The team visited Chellanam, Kumbalanghi and Thoppumpady on Saturday where they visited the computer laboratory at the Kumbalanghi Government High School, set up with local area development fund from K. V. Thomas, MP from Ernakulam. The team visited Kochi Loretto School building; the football ground at the Rajiv Gandhi Stadium and toilet block of St. Sebastianâ€™s HSS, Thoppumpady.